Hello,

Following the completion of the performance and sizing study for the Red Hat Satellite platform, and in line with official Red Hat best-practice recommendations, we have identified the need to increase resources to 48 vCPU and 256 GB RAM in order to ensure optimal performance, stability, and scalability.

Based on the information we have regarding the requirement for a VMware exception when thresholds are exceeded (vCPU > 24 and/or RAM > 192 GB), we have already created a ServiceNow change request to formally track this activity.

